	<h2>Software Architecture</h2>
	This demo is built using <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/"><em>Ruby on Rails</em></a> and the 
	<a href="http://www.oracle.com/database/index.html"><em>Oracle</em></a> database. Ruby on Rails was chosen because it promotes agile and rapid software development.  Oracle was chosen because of its scalability to very large web sites via the RAC cluster configuration, and because of its support for the PL/SQL language.  PL/SQL enables more work to be done in the database and less in the middle tier (Ruby on Rails) servers thus enhancing performance.  The <a href="http://httpd.apache.org/"><em>Apache HTTP Server</em></a> is used together with
	<a href="http://www.modrails.com/"><em>Phusion Passenger</em></a> to deploy the Ruby processes that run the Rails application.

