	<h2>Scaling with Hardware</h2>
	We can build an Oracle RAC cluster tier and a tier of Ruby on Rails servers that function as one high-performance web site.  

	<h2>Custom Look and Feel</h2>
	The CSS stylesheets for this demo site are deliberately very simple.  This makes it easier to create a
	web site design suited to the requirements of the merchant.  

	<h2>Javascript</h2>
	The site will function 100&#37; correctly if a customer disables Javascript in their browser.  In this case,
	some conveniences or visual cues will not be available.  The <a href="http://jquery.com/"><em>jQuery</em></a> library is used to smooth over browser incompatibilities and to provide additional functionality and effects.

	<h2>Credit Card Billing</h2>
	Billing via credit card is done with the
	<a href="http://www.braintreepaymentsolutions.com/"><em>Braintree</em></a> payment gateway.  Braintree was chosen because it supports a payment mode called <em>Transparent Redirect</em> that allows a customer to
	pay by credit card without having credit card information pass through the merchant&apos;web site.
	This makes PCI compliance much simpler. 
	<a href="https://cms.paypal.com/us/cgi-bin/?cmd=_render-content&content_ID=developer/home_US"><em>Paypal Standard</em> and <em>Paypal Pro</em></a> are also supported.  Other payment gateways can be easily added.
	Note that all merchants need to be PCI compliant.  For information on PCI see the <a href="https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org"/><em>PCI Security Standards Council</em></a>.

	<h2>Customer Accounts</h2>
	It is very simple for a customer to create an account &#8212; he or she simply enters a <em>login</em>, a <em>password</em>, and an <em>email address</em>.  Optionally, the account creation process can require email validation.  Password recovery via email is supported. Account creation is kept very simple to maximize the chance the customer will stay on the website.  Alternatively, customers may purchase items without an account.
	If an account is created, the customer may return later to check order status and they will not have to enter billing or shipping addresses again. Log in via <a href="http://openid.net/"><em>OpenID</em></a> is also
	supported.
